	Parliament, 14 February 2023 -The claim that the Speaker of the National Assembly referred to the Members of the Economic Freedom Fighters as “animals” after she ruled that they must be removed from the sitting during the State of the Nation Address on Thursday, is baseless and misleading.
	
	At today’s debate by the joint sitting of Parliament on the address by the President, the Chairperson of the National Council of Provinces, Mr. Amos Masondo, appealed to Members to refrain from repeating the unsubstantiated allegation as he set the record straight.
	
	The unrevised Hansard, a record of the proceedings of the House, confirms that the Speaker’s remark as “phumani, man!”, which is translated “get out, man!”.
	
	The Chairperson, who is co-chairing the joint sitting alongside the Speaker, made this ruling in the House this afternoon.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAENQUIRIES: Moloto Mothapo The President is not a member of Parliament. After an MP is elected as President, he or she loses the seat and the vacancy is filled by the next eligible person from the same party. African National Congress on the provincial list for the province of Gauteng